requirements.contract:
`formalize_query_with_context(query: str, limit: int | None = None) -> str`

      1. Call `await self.query_memory(query, limit)` and unpack the
         3-tuple into `short_episodes`, `long_episodes`, and `summary_list`.
      2. Merge `short_episodes` and `long_episodes` into a single list,
         then sort by `Episode.timestamp` ascending so the oldest appears
         first in the formatted output.
      3. Build the return string:
         - If `summary_list` is non-empty and contains at least one
           non-None entry, include a `&lt;Summary&gt;` block that joins all
           summary strings separated by "\n".
         - If the merged episode list is non-empty, include an
           `&lt;Episodes&gt;` block where each episode's string content appears
           on its own line.
         - Always append `&lt;Query&gt;\n{query}\n&lt;/Query&gt;` at the end.
         - When both summary and episodes are absent (all lists empty),
           return only the `&lt;Query&gt;` block.

      Expected output format (when both context and summary exist):
      ```
      &lt;Summary&gt;
      {summary_strings joined by "\n"}

      &lt;/Summary&gt;
      &lt;Episodes&gt;
      {episode1.content}
      {episode2.content}
      &lt;/Episodes&gt;
      &lt;Query&gt;
      {query}
      &lt;/Query&gt;
      ```
